      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I disagree with meshcollider and promag, and think this information is useful. Or at least I don't understand how it harms anyone. I hate documentation that just gives me a handwavy gloss about how an option is intended to be used without saying what it actually does.\r\n\r\nOf course it would also be good to document wallet endpoints in markdown. There is some text in the [0.15.0 release notes](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/release-notes/release-notes-0.15.0.md#multi-wallet-support) (\"HTTP RPC requests should be send to the...\") that could be moved to [JSON-RPC-interface.md](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/JSON-RPC-interface.md). This could be done here or in a separate PR. I actually remember complaining about lack of API documentation when this feature was first added https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/10849#issuecomment-315731689, and I guess it still doesn't exist.",
